# Security notes for {{SERVER_NAME}}

This server was generated by **mcpgen**. Generated tool handlers are a starting
point, not a finished product. Review the items below before exposing this
server to an AI agent or the network.

## What mcpgen already does

- **Input validation.** Every tool input is validated against a Zod schema by
  the MCP runtime before the handler runs (`registerTool` enforces this).
- **No unsafe interpolation.** All upstream URLs are built in `src/http.ts`:
  path parameters are `encodeURIComponent`-ed and query parameters go through
  `URLSearchParams`. Tool input is never spliced into a URL, shell, SQL, or file
  path as a raw string.
- **Scoped credentials from the environment.** Secrets are read from environment
  variables (see `.env.example`) at runtime and attached to outbound requests in
  one place. No credential is hardcoded in the source.

