## Transport hardening

- The Streamable HTTP transport (`MCPGEN_TRANSPORT=http`) listens on `/mcp` with
  no authentication of the *MCP client* itself. Put it behind an authenticating
  reverse proxy, network policy, or API gateway before exposing it.
- Prefer `stdio` for local, single-user use.

## General

- Scope upstream credentials to the minimum permissions the exposed tools need.
- Log and monitor tool invocations; treat all tool input as untrusted.
- Re-review this file whenever you regenerate or hand-edit the server.
